    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.711/120</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 4898</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-25">October 25,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received November 2.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the Department’s
                    airgram no. A–2323 of October 6, 1943,<note n="39" xml:id="d140fn39">Not
                        printed.</note> concerning the submission of statements from the Military,
                    Naval and Legal Attachés and the Cable Censorship Liaison Officer, to constitute
                    positive justification before the Bureau of the Budget for an allocation of
                    funds assisting the inauguration and operation of cable, telegraph and radio
                    censorship in Cuba. The statements requested are enclosed herewith.<note n="40"
                        xml:id="d140fn40">None printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I can not fail to take this further opportunity of stressing the importance of
                    closing this gap in the censorship of communications which, as may be seen from
                    the enclosures, is necessary both from the negative and positive sides of
                    censorship. I recommend also that the earliest possible action be taken to make
                    the requisite funds available.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spruille Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
